            <abstract id="ref2" label="Abstract">The collection details John E. Pease experience in World War II. He enlisted in the Marines in 1943 he became a member of the Special Weapons Division in which he served in the Pacific Campaign until his discharge in 1946. The collection consists of personal and military manuscripts, news articles, and photographs. The records provide evidence of the massive loss of American life during the battle for Tarawa, and air attacks by the Japanese on American bases.</abstract>
